<dl id="n33180b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n33" href="#n33180b">N33 (VI.B.4)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n33all.htm#n33180b"> 180(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ feather v heart <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n33180b"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[In the Judgement Scene of the Papyrus of Ani]</font> the <mark>heart</mark> of the deceased is being <mark>weighed against the feather</mark> of Ma&acirc;t by Anubis, who scrutinizes the tongue of the balance with great care; close to the pillar of the scales is the monster &Acirc;m-mit, who is ready to devour the heart in the event of its being found light. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1909) lxxxvi</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Probaly moved to <a name="n33298e" href="n33all.htm#n33298e">N33 (VI.B.4):298(e)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
